Definitions "192.com" means 192.com Limited of Unit 8-10 Quayside Lodge, William Morris Way, London, SW6 2UZ; "Personal Information" means information that can be used to uniquely identify a single person; "Service" means the website www.192.com; "You" means you as the user of the Service and "Your" and "Yours" shall be interpreted accordingly.
2. 192.com's privacy commitment 192.com has been providing an online directory service since 1997.

Whilst 192.com endeavours to provide users with the broadest possible set of information , 192.com is also committed to protecting the privacy of any individual who wishes their Personal Information not to be shown in search results.
This Policy sets out the means by which You can have Your Personal Information removed from the Service.
192.com is also committed to keeping Personal Information of users of the Service secure and only to use it for the purposes set out in this Policy and as agreed by You.
192.com is committed to complying with the provisions of the Data Protection Act and is registered with the Information Commissioner's Office under number: Z2501438.
3. Personal Information published on 192.com 192.com publishes Personal Information from the following databases:
The Directory Enquiry Database This is the national directory enquiry database which is licensed to 192.com by British Telecom.
BT collects this information from all the UK's telephone companies and provides the resulting database of numbers to all of the UK's directory enquiry service providers.
If You wish that Your details do not appear in directories such as 192.com or 118 services You need to contact Your telephone service provider who will set You up with Ex-Directory status.
This change will automatically be communicated to all directory enquiry services.
If Your concern is merely to avoid annoying tele-marketing calls, You don't need to go Ex-Directory.
A more effective action is to register with the Telephone Preference Service (TPS) which maintains a database of people that do not wish to receive such calls.
Tele-marketing companies are legally obliged not to call numbers that have been registered on TPS. www.tpsonline.org.uk Electoral Register
There are two versions of the Electoral Register. The Full Electoral Register can only be used for electoral and other restricted purposes.
The Edited Electoral Register was created in 2002 to provide a consented national name and address database that can be used for non-electoral purposes.
Everyone has the right to opt-out of the Edited Electoral Register.

Among the many uses of the Edited Electoral Register is the use by directories such as 192.com, by companies to prevent fraudulent credit card use, and by many charities such as adoption and fostering agencies and organ donation charities.
There are many advantages to being on the Edited Electoral Register.
For convenience, 192.com obtains the Edited Electoral Register from a credit reference agency who in turn obtains the information direct from local authorities.
To opt-out of being listed in the Edited Electoral Register You should contact Your local council or tick the relevant box on the annual voter registration form.
192.com recommends only opting-out of the Edited Electoral Register if You have a specific need.
If Your only concern is to avoid direct marketing, or "junk mail" as it is sometimes called, there is a more effective way than opting-out of the Edited Electoral Register.
This is because the Edited Register is only one source of many of names and addresses for marketing companies.

The Mail Preference Service maintains a list of all those people that do not wish to receive direct marketing and this is used by almost all direct marketing companies to avoid sending such mail: www.mpsonline.org.uk In addition to opting-out of the Edited Electoral Register through Your local council, You may also contact 192.com directly to be removed from the Electoral Registers published on the Service.
To do this please download the record removal form and mail it to the address given.
Company Directors Database The Company Directors Database is a list of all UK company directors which is collated by Companies House.
Company director information is in the public domain to encourage transparency regarding the companies that consumers deal with.
Only under very unusual circumstances will Companies House allow a director's details to be made anonymous.
Should You wish to investigate this possibility please contact Companies House on: +44 (0) 303 1234 500
4. Personal Information collected during registration / payment What Personal Information is collected and why?
If You register with 192.com You will be asked to provide Your name and email address and You will be asked to choose a password for Your account.
This information helps to ensure that Your account is protected and allows 192.com to display private information to You about Your account.
Your e-mail address is used as Your 192.com user name, but it also provides a means of contacting You about Your account, about the Service and to promote our products and services to You.
If You pay to access premium services on the Service it will be necessary to provide Your address, credit / debit card details and date of birth.
This enables the card transaction to be processed including checks to prevent unauthorized use of Your credit card by fraudsters.
In performing these checks Your Personal Information may be disclosed to a registered Credit Reference Agency which may keep a record of that information.
You can rest assured that this is done only to confirm Your identity, that a credit check is not performed and that Your credit rating will be unaffected.
Personal Information collected from You during registration / payment will never be published on the Service.
During registration, we will seek Your agreement to send You the regular 192.com newsletter informing You about the Service and providing offers and promotions.
192.com will also seek Your agreement to share Your contact details with carefully selected partners so that they may send You offers and promotions.

If You do not wish to receive the 192.com newsletter or offers, You can unsubscribe at any time by going to "Your Account", and selecting "change e-mail preferences", or You can write to: Customer Service, 192.com Limited, Units 8-10 Quayside Lodge, William Morris Way, London, SW6 2UZ.
Will 192.com share Personal Information collected during registration / payment with third parties?

Except as specifically set out in this policy, 192.com does not disclose Your Personal Information to any other person or organization except that it may disclose Personal Information to 192.com employees and companies acting as data processors on 192.com's behalf.
Data processors acting on 192.com's behalf may only use the information in line with 192.com's instructions.

In addition 192.com may disclose Personal Information if required to do so by law or in the good faith that such disclosure is necessary to: (i) comply with legal process or assist law enforcement agencies including the Police and the Information Commissioner's Office; (ii) respond to claims of a violation of the rights of third parties; or (iii) protect the rights, property or safety of 192.com, its users, or the public.
5. Search Logs What search logs are collected and why?

192.com keeps logs of all searches conducted by users of the Service (whether registered or not) including the IP (Internet Protocol) address from which a user session was conducted, the identity of the searcher (where we have it), the date and time of each search made and the results provided in response to a search.

This information may be used: i) to assist in improving the nature and quality of the Service; ii) to advise individuals whose Personal Information appears in search results that their Personal Information has been displayed to a user of the Service and, if the searching user's identity is known, this information may be passed to the individual whose Personal Information has been displayed; and iii) 192.com also reserves the right to pass on such logs to the Police in the event that it might assist with an investigation.
6. Use of Cookies on 192.com What are Cookies?
A Cookie is a text file containing small amounts of information that will be downloaded to Your computer when You use 192.com.

Each time You return to 192.com this information will be automatically sent back to the 192.com servers enabling it to identify the computer that is connected to the Service and to recall Your personal settings for use of the Service.
Cookies do not contain Personal Information. Cookies do lots of jobs and are a commonplace tool used by all major websites.
They enable things such as navigating between pages efficiently, remembering user preferences, and generally improving the user experience.
They can also help to ensure that adverts You see online are more relevant to You and Your interests.
There is legal regulation around how cookies are used and the agreement required from users and 192.com is committed to meeting these requirements.
What types of cookie does 192.com use and obtaining Your agreement? The three categories of cookie that 192.com uses are:
Category 1 - Strictly necessary cookies These cookies are essential in order to enable You to move around the Service and use its features.
Without these cookies, 192.com could not provide the Service to You.
You may not use our Service if you do not wish these cookies to be placed on Your computer.
Category 2 - Internal cookies (sometimes known as "performance" and "monitoring" cookies)
These cookies collect information about how visitors to 192.com use the site, for instance which pages are used most often, and allow 192.com to remember choices You make such as Your user name.
The information collected using these cookies cannot track Your browsing activity on other web sites.
By using 192.com, You agree that these cookies can be placed on your computer.
Category 3 - Targeting cookies These cookies are used to deliver adverts more relevant to You and Your interests.
They may also limit the number of times You see a particular advertisement as well as measure the effectiveness of advertising campaigns.
They are usually placed by third party advertising networks with 192.com's permission.

They remember that You have visited a particular web site and this information together with information on Your inferred interests (based on how you have used that web site) is shared with other organizations such as advertisers.
You can choose not to have these cookies placed on Your computer by going to: www.youronlinechoices.com/uk/your-ad-choices Unless You opt-out
You agree that our partners may place these cookies on Your computer.
7. Acceptance of this Policy By using the Service
You signify Your acceptance of the 192.com Privacy Policy.
If You do not accept this Policy, You may not use the Service.
192.com may change this Privacy Policy at any time by posting a revised version via the Privacy Policy links on the Service.
We recommend that You frequently check for updates. Continued use of the Service following the posting of any changes will signify Your acceptance of those changes.
8. Help to improve our Service Your comments are important to us and help us improve the service we offer.
If You have any comments regarding our Privacy Policy, please contact us or write to: Customer Services, 192.com Limited, Units 8-10 Quayside Lodge, William Morris Way, London, SW6 2UZ.
